The stigma attached to (ex) wives and ex-husbands, makes KL political leaders to be cautious about establishing second marriages. Indeed, in the last sixteen years, no less than five KL passed 3rd marriages, but the convincing with bloated divorces was only achieved by the Liberal-Democratic Party leader, Mr. Kubatbek Baibolov in 2007. Likely very few sons and daughters of KL marriage separatists would marry KL themselves. It is doubtful that the tainted KL professionals will get “enough weight” to establish marital relations in the society. They would do more trouble than benefit to their parental families if they will acquiesce to critics of family separationists.

First sentence. Agree.

Second sentence. Disagree. The stigma attached to divorcees is far greater in the Western world where divorce is so widespread. Guys here bitch and moan about KY people, but they are nothing in comparison to how Western people see divorcees. Not sure which “powerful strata of KL society refuse second and third marriages”, but divorce is the reason a lot of prominent KL people died alone. But second marriage matters not as the third often leads to death.
